CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 2, 1946, pg. 17 reads: "Strike Aid - Men of the Hotel and Restaurant Employees Union, Local 237, distribute hot coffee and doughnuts to let striking steel workers know they're with them. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Striking steelworkers receiving coffee from men of the Hotel and Restaurant Employees Union, Local 237, girl saluting in foreground
